The increase in production in the euro area slowed in August to the lowest point in the last 13 months, according to a closely observed study.
The final Markit Purchasing Manager Index of the Manufacturing Industry (PMI) fell to 50.7 in August, after a 51.8 in July.
An indication above 50 indicates an expansion.
New orders declined and factories experienced burglaries at a time of rising tensions between the EU and Russia over Ukraine.
